    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-08-31T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="629"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d629">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6363 Manchuria/42: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-31T14:00:00+09:00"
                            >August 31, 1934—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 31—5:37 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>191. Department’s 149, August 29, 5 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>I entirely concur with the Department’s views and have therefore today
                        transmitted the Department’s informal memorandum to the Minister for Foreign
                        Affairs.</item>
                    <pb facs="0818" n="728" xml:id="pg_728"/>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>I have been informed by Mr. Goold, general manager in Japan of the
                        Standard-Vacuum Oil Company, that the Standard, Rising Sun (Shell interests)
                        and Texas Oil Companies have all agreed not to submit bids for the supply of
                        crude oil for the Manchuria Oil Company which is now asking for bids for
                        crude oil for the refinery being built at Dairen.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Despite reports from Mukden that the proposed oil monopoly might be
                        changed to a licensing system, Hashimoto, president of the Manchuria Oil
                        Company, recently told Goold that the monopoly plan would certainly be
                        carried out but that the date of enforcement had not been fixed.</item>
                </list>
                <p>Repeated to Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
